There is still time to complete the U.S. Census! Census workers will begin going door-to-door to survey households that have not yet submitted a census on August 11.

Thank you to those who have already completed it! The Census affects funding for important programs that benefit our students such as special education programs, Head Start, after-school programs, classroom technology, food assistance programs, as well as maternal and child health programs.

Respond TODAY at 2020Census.gov! #EachKansanCounts

Just a reminder that Walk-In Enrollment is TODAY (August 3) in all USD 490 school buildings from 8:00 a.m. to 7:00 p.m. and at the District Office from 8:00 a.m. - 4:30 p.m. Masks will be required and we will be checking temperatures for all visitors.

Save a trip by completing it online at home! If you have any questions, building staff are available to assist you by phone.

For more information, please visit the Learning Resources and COVID-19 page on our website. This page is located under the News tab and will be updated as often as we have new information to share related to the COVID-19 pandemic and our schools.

Beginning today, June 1, USD 490 buildings will begin their summer hours. In an effort to reduce energy costs and conserve district funds, staff will work four ten-hour days Monday - Thursday. Buildings will be open to the public normal hours on those days through June 15.

The District Office will be open to the public 7:30 a.m. - 4:30 p.m. Monday - Thursday for the remainder of the summer. If you have any questions, please contact us at 316-322-4800.

Have a great summer!

Have a great summer!

There has been a slight change to meal distribution beginning today, April 6. Meals will only be distributed on Mondays and Wednesdays. They will be at the same times and locations, but Wednesday's meal pick up will include three breakfasts and lunches instead of two.

Meals can be picked up in the bus lanes of Blackmore, Skelly, and El Dorado High School from 11:00 a.m. - 1:00 p.m. and at Quail Ridge and Walnut River apartment complexes from 11:30 a.m. - 12:30 p.m. Anyone 18 years old or younger desiring a meal must be present at the time the meal is being picked up. Meals will be handed into vehicles so students can stay in the vehicle to receive the meals. Children are also able to walk up to meal distribution sites and take their meals to-go.
#partofthepride #inthistogether

post_text: Any lunch money remaining in a student's account at the end of the school year is automatically rolled over to the next school year. If you would like to have your child's remaining lunch money refunded instead, please let us know and we will be happy to get a refund processed for you. Email your name, your child's name and that you want a refund to usd490@eldoradoschools.org . We will get them processed as quickly as possible. You may also call your child's school office or the district office after they reopen on Monday, March 23. #partofthepride

post_text: Did you know that on Monday, each child 18 years or younger will receive 2 breakfasts & 2 lunches? Monday meals cover Monday AND Tuesday! #partofthepride #mealsforALL5days
shared_text:
El Dorado Schools
March 18 at 6:31 PM 

Beginning Monday, March 23, USD 490 & OPAA! will provide meal pick up on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday. Meals can be picked up in the bus drives of Blackmore, Skelly, and El Dorado High School from 11-1 and at Quail Ridge and Walnut River from 11:30-12:30. Any child ages 18 or younger desiring a meal must be present at the time the meal is being picked up. Food containers will be handed into vehicles so students can stay in the vehicle to receive the meals.

post_text: OPAA! in El Dorado, KS knows how to have FUN WITH A PURPOSE ! After a delicious, nutritious breakfast at Grandview Elementary, students can enjoy a little Thanksgiving fun on our draw wall. After the students finish eating in the mornings, they can come have a little fun before heading off to class! The students love it and it is a great way to start the day! Thank you Peggy for all that you do! #partofthepride #gators #opaafood

post_text: The Butler County Health Department ran out of the Meningitis vaccine during their Walk-In Immunization Clinic on August 9. They have ordered more for their next clinic on September 14 (9 a.m. - 1 p.m.). Students who have not yet received the required immunizations will be allowed to start school, but need to have their immunizations up-to-date by September 24. If your student is exempt from immunizations, please send a letter to your child's school office notifying them of the exemption.

Today is Walk-In Enrollment! If you have not already completed the online enrollment for your child(ren), Walk-In Enrollment is taking place from 8:00 a.m. - 7:00 p.m. in all USD 490 schools.

To complete enrollment for a returning student, please log into your PowerSchool Parent account: https://powerschool.eldoradoschools.org/public/home.html

To complete enrollment for a new student, please use the new student link: https://registration.powerschool.com/family/gosnap.aspx?action=19607&culture=en

Back-to-school mailings will be sent out at the end of this week. They will include your child's class schedule, bus information, and other important reminders for the start of the new school year, so please make sure your address is current when completing enrollment.

From all of us at USD 490...thank you for being #partofthepride! We look forward to another great school year with each of you.

post_text:
Just a couple of helpful hints for enrollment:

RevTrak's online payment system does not work in Internet Explorer. Please make sure you are using Safari, Firefox, or Chrome to complete online payments. The login for Student Food and Fee Payments is the same as the one you use to enroll your students.

If you are getting an error after the Health page, please check the text boxes for special characters < or >. The system will error out if these are present in any text box. Simply deleting them will allow you to continue with enrollment. If you don't immediately see any text boxes, please click "Yes" and make sure there is not data carried over from last year in one of those boxes. If the info is no longer relevant, simply delete it and then click "No."

If you find yourself getting frustrated, please give us a call at the District Office 316-322-4800. We'd be happy to assist you.

USD 490 bus driver Miranda Cecchini-Roosevelt placed sixth in the Mini Bus Competition during the International School Bus Competition on July 20 and 21.

The competition included drivers from 30 U.S. states and Canada. There were 37 competitors in the Conventional Competition, 22 in the Transit Competition, and 12 in the Mini Bus Competition.

Christy Fletcher also attended the competition and served as a judge for the Back Up Alley event. Next year's competition will take place in New York.

#partofthepride

post_text:
The El Dorado High School football team volunteered time after practice to help redistribute rubber mulch on Skelly Elementary's playground on July 16.

In just over an hour, the team was able to redistribute over 40,000 pounds of rubber mulch across the playground, improving the play surface for more than 300 elementary school children who will enjoy the playground during the 2019-2020 school year.

"This is what being family and #partofthepride is all about," Head Football Coach Wes Bell said. "It ensures that future wildcats have a safe place to play."

The team worked as a unit to form bucket brigades to haul the rubber and used shovels and rakes to level the surface.

"The maintenance department really appreciated the help," USD 490 Electrician Tony Goossen said.

USD 490 classes will resume on August 13, 2019.
